Company Overview
**SHUWEIHAT ASIA POWER COMPANY** S3 power plant will be operated by Shuweihat Asia O & M Company which is a 51% : 49% joint venture by Korea  Electric Power Corporation of Korea and Sumitomo Corporation of Japan respectively. With the intention to provide secure, safe and reliable supplies of water and electricity and to encourage private sector investment, in the early 1998, ADWEA’ embarked on the privatisation of the water and power industry. In the process, the ADWEA has formed almost 9 private sector companies in Abu Dhabi & Fujairah, with different multinational companies engaged in the energy. 3 plants in Taweelah, 2 plants in Shuweihat and 2 plant in Fujairah and 1 at Umm Al Nar. The third plant that is coming up in Shuweihat is the 9th plant and is called S3 or Shuweihat Asia Power Company with joint participation of Sumitomo of Japan and Korean Electric Power Corporation of Korea. S3 power plant will be producing 1600 MW of power. ADWEA holds 60% in this plant as local investor and Sumitomo and KEPCO hold 20.4% and 19.6% respectively.It is believed that this company in the private sector will encourage private sector investment, create new employment opportunities, accelerate economic and social development.It is envisaged that the commissioning of this project will help to meet ever-growing demand for electricity in the Emirate of Abu Dhabi by reliable supply of power to the requirement of the Government of Abu Dhabi. When commissioned, this project will produce and supply anything around 15% of power requirement of the Abu Dhabi Emirate.Shuweihat Asia Power Company (called as S3 Power Plant) will be managed by Executive Managing Director who is ably assisted by a team of professional and technocrats to bring this project up in a limited time frame with early power in March 2013. The plant is expected to commence its full commercial operation by March 2014.
